PulseAudio introspection callbacks are invoked once with eol = -1 when the
query errors (e.g. pa_context_get_card_info_by_name on a card that doesn't
exist yet, which happens in the window between the AACP L2CAP connection
coming up and WirePlumber recreating the bluez card on reconnect). The
`eol > 0` checks skipped pa_threaded_mainloop_signal in that case, so
waitForOperation blocked forever and froze the Qt main thread, silently
killing ear detection until the daemon was restarted.

Signal the mainloop on any end-of-list, including the error case.

--- a/media/pulseaudiocontroller.cpp
+++ b/media/pulseaudiocontroller.cpp
@@ -125,7 +125,7 @@

     auto callback = [](pa_context *c, const pa_sink_info *info, int eol, void *userdata) {
         CallbackData *d = static_cast<CallbackData*>(userdata);
-        if (eol > 0)
+        if (eol)
         {
             pa_threaded_mainloop_signal(d->mainloop, 0);
             return;
@@ -208,7 +208,7 @@

     auto callback = [](pa_context *c, const pa_card_info *info, int eol, void *userdata) {
         CallbackData *d = static_cast<CallbackData*>(userdata);
-        if (eol > 0)
+        if (eol)
         {
             pa_threaded_mainloop_signal(d->mainloop, 0);
             return;
@@ -253,7 +253,7 @@

     auto callback = [](pa_context *c, const pa_card_info *info, int eol, void *userdata) {
         CallbackData *d = static_cast<CallbackData*>(userdata);
-        if (eol > 0)
+        if (eol)
         {
             pa_threaded_mainloop_signal(d->mainloop, 0);
             return;
